(184, NULL, NULL, 'MG-R-20260119-48382', 'Capt Krishan Gopal', '9324384858', 'kgopal1962@gmail.com', 'MuscleGrid India SOLAR SENSATION 4.2KVA 48V Hybrid Solar Inverter 6 AI Modes', 'MG2441M42C03MG2441M42C04', '72125000029207', NULL, '2024-12-10', 'uploads/invoices/184/invoice.jpeg', NULL, 'phone', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Krishan Gopal <kgopal1962@gmail.com>\r\nSat, Jan 17, 8:24 PM (2 days ago)\r\nto Mani\r\n\r\nSubject / Message: Fault Report – Instant Overload on Battery Connection (Invoice ID 5877542)\r\n\r\nDear Muscle Grid Support Team,\r\n\r\nThanks a ton for the appointment. \r\n\r\nWe are in the process of installing two Muscle Grid 4.2 kVA / 48 V Hybrid Solar Inverters supplied against Invoice Order ID: 5877542 (Oct 2024).\r\n\r\nBoth inverters are exhibiting the same fault during installation:\r\n\r\nInstant “Overload” indication immediately on battery connection\r\n\r\nNo AC load connected\r\n\r\n48 V Lead-acid battery bank\r\n\r\nBatteries are healthy and within normal voltage range\r\n\r\nFault appears the moment batteries are connected\r\n\r\nBased on installation checks and elimination of external causes, the issue appears to be internal to the inverter, most likely related to:\r\n\r\nDC bus capacitor / DC input stage or input MOSFET / current sensing circuit, causing abnormal inrush detection.\r\n\r\nThis behavior is identical on both units, indicating a possible manufacturing or batch-related issue rather than site conditions.\r\n\r\nWe request urgent technical guidance / service support and advise on repair or replacement under warranty, as repeated battery connection may risk further internal damage.\r\n\r\nKindly advise the next steps at the earliest.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nCapt. Krishan Gopal\r\n\r\nMaster Mariner \r\n+91 9324384858', NULL, 'Capt. Krishan Gopal , 002 SHAILESH CHS PLOT 09 RD 16 SEC 11 NEW PANVEL NAVI MUMBI -410206. kgopal1962@gmail.com,', 'NAVI MUMBAI', '410206', '0000-00-00', 'Resolved on Call', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2026-01-24 08:28:39', '2026-01-19 08:55:52', '2026-01-24 08:28:39', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
